FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31002
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1783923682
OL,3,CJannik Sinner defends Wimbledon title
OL,4,Cafter battling to defeat Alexander
OL,5,CZverev
OL,7,FIt was also a 100th grand slam match
OL,8,Fwin for the world number one, who
OL,9,Fearned royal approval from the Prince
OL,10,Fand Princess of Wales, Prince George
OL,11,Fand Princess Charlotte in the front
OL,12,Frow of the Royal Box.
OL,14,FAfter losing nine matches in a row and
OL,15,F14 sets against Sinner, Zverev knew he
OL,16,Fhad to do something different and his
OL,17,Fintention was clear from the start.
OL,19,FHe was the better player overall at
OL,20,Fthe first tie-break.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31003
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1783923682
OL,3,CJannik Sinner defends Wimbledon title
OL,4,Cafter battling to defeat Alexander
OL,5,CZverev
OL,7,FZverev, who will overtake Alcaraz to
OL,8,Fbecome world number two on Monday,
OL,9,Fseemed to have the edge still until
OL,10,Fthe next tie-break, when Sinner's
OL,11,Fforehand clicked into gear at just the
OL,12,Fright moment and suddenly he was the
OL,13,Fplayer dictating the rallies.
OL,15,FAn understated fist pump towards his
OL,16,Fteam greeted a missed Zverev backhand
OL,17,Fon set point and the second seed
OL,18,Fheaded off to the bathroom with the
OL,19,Fmomentum of the match abruptly shifted.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31004
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1783923682
OL,3,CJannik Sinner defends Wimbledon title
OL,4,Cafter battling to defeat Alexander
OL,5,CZverev
OL,7,FUnexpectedly, it was Zverev who had
OL,8,Fthe first look in the third set, with
OL,9,FSinner playing a shaky game to cough
OL,10,Fup a break point at 3-3, but he was
OL,11,Ffortunate that his opponent slipped
OL,12,Fbehind the baseline.
OL,14,FZverev initially looked in trouble as
OL,15,Fhe held his right knee but Sinner
OL,16,Fheaded round the net to give him a
OL,17,Fhand up and play soon continued.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
